The paper introduces PyRobot, a robotics framework for research and benchmarking. The paper discusses how PyRobot provides a high-level interface on top of ROS, which is a popular robotics middleware. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions that PyRobot is designed to enable researchers to build high-level AI applications, which suggests that it may also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also mentions that PyRobot provides access to robotics datasets, algorithm implementations, and models, which suggests that it may belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses how PyRobot abstracts away details about low-level controllers and inter-process communication, which suggests that it may also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
